g.text: Test power supply and determne if FB1 and R19 are needed.

g.desc: Test power supply and determne if FB1 and R19 are needed.

g.text: Find out proper capacitance (range) of C3, C9, C11, D1.

g.desc: Find out proper capacitance (range) of C3, C9, C11, D1.

g.text: Do not connect voltages above 100 V!

g.desc: Do not connect voltages above 100 V!

g.text: Input waveforms max. 50 Vp-p. (due to distortion)

g.desc: Input waveforms max. 50 Vp-p. (due to distortion)

g.text: Find out values of delinearising resistors R11, R12 for optimal user experience during tuning.

g.desc: Find out values of delinearising resistors R11, R12 for optimal user experience during tuning.

g.text: Test noise impact of R14 and R16, test with vlaues increasing in decades.

g.desc: Test noise impact of R14 and R16, test with vlaues increasing in decades.

g.text: Find out value of offseting resistor R17 for optimal user experience during tuning.

g.desc: Find out value of offseting resistor R17 for optimal user experience during tuning.

g.text: Try to replace BF998 with non-EOL component.

g.desc: Try to replace BF998 with non-EOL component.

g.text: Optimise value of L1, try on multiple devices.

g.desc: Optimise value of L1, try on multiple devices.

g.text: The PCBite holder has M4 screw and external diameter of 13 mm.

g.desc: The PCBite holder has M4 screw and external diameter of 13 mm.

g.text: Impedance controlled traces are designed for JLC PCB JLC04161H-3313 stackup.

g.desc: Impedance controlled traces are designed for JLC PCB JLC04161H-3313 stackup.

g.text: 50R traces need to have L2 removed and coupled to L3.

g.desc: 50R traces need to have L2 removed and coupled to L3.

g.text: The resistor protects external gear from damage!

g.desc: The resistor protects external gear from damage!

g.text: Make sure that ext. gear does not present voltage >10 V.

g.desc: Make sure that ext. gear does not present voltage >10 V.

g.text: Optimise values of degenerating resistors, try on multiple devices.

g.desc: Optimise values of degenerating resistors, try on multiple devices.

g.text: 1) Perform this calibration in ESD safe environment!

g.desc: 1) Perform this calibration in ESD safe environment!

g.text: Short the input, power up the probe (with VNA disconnected).

g.desc: Short the input, power up the probe (with VNA disconnected).

g.text: Not shorting the input may affect the measurement.

g.desc: Not shorting the input may affect the measurement.

g.text: 2) Connect VNA, measure output impedance of the probe.

g.desc: 2) Connect VNA, measure output impedance of the probe.

g.text: Tune the bias on gate 2 to get 50 Ohm output.

g.desc: Tune the bias on gate 2 to get 50 Ohm output.

g.text: 3) Disconnect VNA, reconnect it to measure S21 of the probe.

g.desc: 3) Disconnect VNA, reconnect it to measure S21 of the probe.

g.text: (If varicap tuning is assembled, set it to highest possible voltage.)

g.desc: (If varicap tuning is assembled, set it to highest possible voltage.)

g.text: Tune the input capacitor to get 10:1 (-20 dB) response.

g.desc: Tune the input capacitor to get 10:1 (-20 dB) response.

g.text: 4) (If assembled, use the varicap tuning to fine-tune the gain).

g.desc: 4) (If assembled, use the varicap tuning to fine-tune the gain).

g.text: If varicap tuning is not used, change bias to fine-tune gain.

g.desc: If varicap tuning is not used, change bias to fine-tune gain.

g.text: 5) Re-measure the output impedance. If out of spec, repeat these steps.

g.desc: 5) Re-measure the output impedance. If out of spec, repeat these steps.

g.text: This is needed because the parameters are not fully independent.

g.desc: This is needed because the parameters are not fully independent.

g.text: G2 bias has effect on peaking around roll-off (lower voltage =

g.desc: G2 bias has effect on peaking around roll-off (lower voltage =

g.text: 1) If desired gain cannot be achieved, change C3.

g.desc: 1) If desired gain cannot be achieved, change C3.

g.text: 2) If output impedance cannot be achieved, change R10.

g.desc: 2) If output impedance cannot be achieved, change R10.

g.text: 3) If varicap tuning is too narrow/broad, change C11.

g.desc: 3) If varicap tuning is too narrow/broad, change C11.

g.text: Too large C11 or too steep D1 can introduce non-linearity.

g.desc: Too large C11 or too steep D1 can introduce non-linearity.

g.text: 4) R11, R12 and R18 delinearise the trimmers to make tuning easier.

g.desc: 4) R11, R12 and R18 delinearise the trimmers to make tuning easier.

g.text: 5) Trimmer C9 has screw connected to input to make tuning easier.

g.desc: 5) Trimmer C9 has screw connected to input to make tuning easier.

g.text: (The input is low impedance source, net after the capacitor is not.)

g.desc: (The input is low impedance source, net after the capacitor is not.)

g.text: 6) For tuning C9, use low capacitance isolated tuning screwdriver.

g.desc: 6) For tuning C9, use low capacitance isolated tuning screwdriver.

g.text: Never tune the probe when connected to dangerous voltages!

g.desc: Never tune the probe when connected to dangerous voltages!

g.text: 7) In case of bad low bandwidth, change L1.

g.desc: 7) In case of bad low bandwidth, change L1.

g.text: 8) In case of instability, notches and peaks at >500 MHz, change R7-9.

g.desc: 8) In case of instability, notches and peaks at >500 MHz, change R7-9.

g.text: 9) After soldering, always clean solder residue!

g.desc: 9) After soldering, always clean solder residue!

g.text: 10) Clockwise rotation of RV2 increases gain.

g.desc: 10) Clockwise rotation of RV2 increases gain.

g.text: 11) Clockwise rotation of RV3 increases current, decreases impedance.

g.desc: 11) Clockwise rotation of RV3 increases current, decreases impedance.

g.text: Critical components have MPNs assigned, except for BF998 (look on eBay).

g.desc: Critical components have MPNs assigned, except for BF998 (look on eBay).

g.text: BF998 with MOW marking may be fake, genuine are MOs or MOp :-)

g.desc: BF998 with MOW marking may be fake, genuine are MOs or MOp :-)

g.text: MOP with a bar above "p" has reversed footprint!

g.desc: MOP with a bar above "p" has reversed footprint!

g.text: This probe is nonlinear, distortion increases with measured amplitude.

g.desc: This probe is nonlinear, distortion increases with measured amplitude.

g.text: Above 50 Vp-p, distortion may increase due to protective diodes on G2.

g.desc: Above 50 Vp-p, distortion may increase due to protective diodes on G2.

g.text: The whole PCB shall be shielded, ideally by a 3D printed cover which

g.desc: The whole PCB shall be shielded, ideally by a 3D printed cover which

g.text: would be either covered by copper tape or coated with carbon and

g.desc: would be either covered by copper tape or coated with carbon and

g.text: Tuning range should be about 2.5 dB using C9 and 1 dB using D1.

g.desc: Tuning range should be about 2.5 dB using C9 and 1 dB using D1.

g.text: Most low frequency noise will probably come from thermal noise of R14.

g.desc: Most low frequency noise will probably come from thermal noise of R14.

g.text: Use only RF capacitors with low losses, ideally suited for >5 GHz!

g.desc: Use only RF capacitors with low losses, ideally suited for >5 GHz!

g.text: Find out value of delinearising resistor R18 for optimal user experience during tuning.

g.desc: Find out value of delinearising resistor R18 for optimal user experience during tuning.
